[SN]TITLE[SN]
Boy, nine, knocked down and injured in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A nine-year-old boy is being treated in hospital after being knocked down by a car in the east end of Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He was struck by a dark-coloured Honda CRV car on Springboig Road, near Threestonehill Avenue, Shettleston, at about 11:15 on Saturday.
The boy is in a stable condition in the Queen Elizabeth University Hospital. The 45-year-old driver was uninjured.
Police are trying to establish the circumstances surrounding the accident and have appealed for witnesses.
